# Styling Conventions

## Color Palette

TREND uses a baroque gold and white luxury theme:

```css
:root {
  --gold-primary: #C9A227;
  --gold-light: #D4AF37;
  --gold-dark: #8B7355;
  --burgundy: #722F37;
  --burgundy-dark: #4A1C23;
  --white: #FFFFFF;
  --cream: #FAF8F0;
  --cream-dark: #F5F0E6;
  --black: #1A1A1A;
  --charcoal: #2C2C2C;
  --gray: #6B6B6B;
  --gray-light: #A0A0A0;
}
```

## Typography

```css
:root {
  --font-display: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
  --font-body: 'Montserrat', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
}
```

## CSS Best Practices

### Use CSS Custom Properties
```css
.button {
  background: var(--gold-primary);
  color: var(--black);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}
```

### BEM-like Naming
```css
.service-card {
  padding: 40px;
}

.service-card__icon {
  font-size: 2rem;
}

.service-card__title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
}
```

### Responsive Design
```css
.hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(3rem, 10vw, 7rem);
  letter-spacing: 8px;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .hero-title {
    letter-spacing: 15px;
  }
}
```

## Component Styling Patterns

### Colocate Styles
```
components/
  ServiceCard/
    ServiceCard.jsx
    ServiceCard.css
    index.js
```

### Import Styles in Component
```jsx
import './ServiceCard.css'

export const ServiceCard = ({ icon, title }) => {
  return (
    <div className="service-card">
      <div className="service-card__icon">{icon}</div>
      <h3 className="service-card__title">{title}</h3>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Luxury Design Principles

### Transitions and Animations
```css
.btn {
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.btn:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 30px rgba(201, 162, 39, 0.3);
}
```

### Ornamental Elements
Use subtle decorative elements consistent with baroque theme:

```css
.ornament {
  width: 60px;
  height: 2px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold-primary), transparent);
  margin: 20px auto;
}
```

### Shadow and Depth
```css
:root {
  --shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  --shadow-gold: 0 4px 30px rgba(201, 162, 39, 0.3);
}
```

## Slider Container Sizing

Three.js slider containers use fixed aspect ratios matching the image dimensions passed to the `Slide` constructor:

```css
.hero-slider {
  width: 280px;
  height: 420px;
}

.gallery-three-container {
  width: 300px;
  height: 400px;
}
```

Hero sliders use a 2:3 portrait ratio (width 70, height 105 in Three.js units).
Gallery sliders use a 3:4 portrait ratio (width 120, height 160 in Three.js units).

## Mobile Fallback for Sliders

On mobile devices the Three.js sliders are disabled entirely. Replace them with a CSS crossfade:

```css
.image-crossfade {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.image-crossfade__img {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 1.5s ease-in-out;
}

.image-crossfade__img--active {
  opacity: 1;
}
```

Use `useIsMobile()` to conditionally render either the Three.js slider or the CSS fallback. The crossfade should cycle images with a 4-second interval using `setInterval` in a `useEffect`.
